        <title>Git Committer Statistics</title>
        <published>2026-03-14T00:00:00+00:00</published>
        <updated>2026-03-14T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
        <author>
            <name>Jason Short</name>
        </author>
        <link rel="alternate" href="https://jashort.github.io/blog/git-committer-statistics/" type="text/html"/>
        <id>https://jashort.github.io/blog/git-committer-statistics/</id>
        
            <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;A few options for getting committer statistics for a git repository:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;print-lines-per-author-with-git-summary-command&quot;&gt;Print lines per author with &lt;code&gt;git summary&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; command&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(from the &lt;a rel=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;tj&#x2F;git-extras&#x2F;tree&#x2F;main&quot;&gt;git-extras&lt;&#x2F;a&gt; package: (&lt;code&gt;brew install git-extras&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; on macOS)&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;giallo z-code&quot;&gt;&lt;code data-lang=&quot;shellscript&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-entity z-name z-function&quot;&gt;git&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-string&quot;&gt; summary --line&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;pre&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;giallo z-code&quot;&gt;&lt;code data-lang=&quot;shellsession&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-text&quot;&gt;project     :     test&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-text&quot;&gt;lines       :     1124&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-text&quot;&gt;authors     :&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-text&quot;&gt;  1103 Alice        98.1%&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-text&quot;&gt;    21 Bob           1.9%&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;pre&gt;&lt;h2 id=&quot;print-number-of-commits-with-the-git-shortlog-command&quot;&gt;Print number of commits with the &lt;code&gt;git shortlog&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; command:&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;giallo z-code&quot;&gt;&lt;code data-lang=&quot;shellscript&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-entity z-name z-function&quot;&gt;git&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-string&quot;&gt; shortlog -s -n -c&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;pre&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;giallo z-code&quot;&gt;&lt;code data-lang=&quot;shellsession&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-text&quot;&gt; 10  Alice&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-text&quot;&gt;  3  Bob&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;pre&gt;</content>
        <summary type="html">Show committer statistics for a git repository</summary>
        </entry><entry xml:lang="en">
        <title>Tmux and Copy to Clipboard</title>
        <published>2026-02-16T00:00:00+00:00</published>
        <updated>2026-02-16T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
        <author>
            <name>Jason Short</name>
        </author>
        <link rel="alternate" href="https://jashort.github.io/blog/tmux-copy/" type="text/html"/>
        <id>https://jashort.github.io/blog/tmux-copy/</id>
        
            <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Problem: Automatic copy to clipboard doesn’t work&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;When ssh’d to a remote server&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Running &lt;code&gt;tmux&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;From a Ghostty terminal window&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But does work:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;When not running &lt;code&gt;tmux&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;, everything else the same.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Solution:
On the remote server, update `~&#x2F;.tmux.conf and add the line:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;giallo z-code&quot;&gt;&lt;code data-lang=&quot;plain&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;set -g allow-passthrough on&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;References:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a rel=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;anomalyco&#x2F;opencode&#x2F;issues&#x2F;4283#issuecomment-3909686321&quot;&gt;GitHub Issue&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
</content>
        <summary type="html">Errors validating certificates when running inside a minimal Docker image?</summary>
        </entry><entry xml:lang="en">
        <title>Tmux, Ghostty, and Shift-Enter</title>
        <published>2026-02-15T00:00:00+00:00</published>
        <updated>2026-02-15T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
        <author>
            <name>Jason Short</name>
        </author>
        <link rel="alternate" href="https://jashort.github.io/blog/tmux-ghostty-shift-enter/" type="text/html"/>
        <id>https://jashort.github.io/blog/tmux-ghostty-shift-enter/</id>
        
            <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Problem: Shift-enter doesn’t work&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;When ssh’d to a remote server&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Running &lt;code&gt;tmux&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;From a Ghostty terminal window&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But does work:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;When not running &lt;code&gt;tmux&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;, everything else the same.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Solution:
Update Ghostty settings and add the line:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;giallo z-code&quot;&gt;&lt;code data-lang=&quot;plain&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;keybind = shift+enter=text:\x1b\r&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On the remote server, update `~&#x2F;.tmux.conf and add the line:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;giallo z-code&quot;&gt;&lt;code data-lang=&quot;plain&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;set -s extended-keys on&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;References:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a rel=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;anomalyco&#x2F;opencode&#x2F;issues&#x2F;1505#issuecomment-3388659338&quot;&gt;GitHub Issue&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
</content>
        <summary type="html">Getting shift-enter working inside tmux</summary>
        </entry><entry xml:lang="en">
        <title>Certificates in Docker Containers</title>
        <published>2026-01-26T00:00:00+00:00</published>
        <updated>2026-01-26T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
        <author>
            <name>Jason Short</name>
        </author>
        <link rel="alternate" href="https://jashort.github.io/blog/certificates-in-docker/" type="text/html"/>
        <id>https://jashort.github.io/blog/certificates-in-docker/</id>
        
            <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;If you’re using a minimal image, you might need to add ca-certificates:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;giallo z-code&quot;&gt;&lt;code data-lang=&quot;docker&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-keyword&quot;&gt;FROM&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source&quot;&gt; alpine &lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-keyword&quot;&gt;AS&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source&quot;&gt; certs&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-keyword&quot;&gt;RUN&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source&quot;&gt; apk add --no-cache ca-certificates&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-keyword&quot;&gt;FROM&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source&quot;&gt; scratch&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-keyword&quot;&gt;COPY&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source&quot;&gt; --from=certs &#x2F;etc&#x2F;ssl&#x2F;certs&#x2F;ca-certificates.crt &#x2F;etc&#x2F;ssl&#x2F;certs&#x2F;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-keyword&quot;&gt;COPY&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source&quot;&gt; my-go-binary &#x2F;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-keyword&quot;&gt;CMD&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source&quot;&gt; [&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-string&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&#x2F;my-go-binary&amp;quot;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source&quot;&gt;]&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;pre&gt;</content>
        <summary type="html">Errors validating certificates when running inside a minimal Docker image?</summary>
        </entry><entry xml:lang="en">
        <title>Joining Python Paths</title>
        <published>2025-08-26T00:00:00+00:00</published>
        <updated>2025-08-26T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
        <author>
            <name>Jason Short</name>
        </author>
        <link rel="alternate" href="https://jashort.github.io/blog/python-joining-directories/" type="text/html"/>
        <id>https://jashort.github.io/blog/python-joining-directories/</id>
        
            <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Joining a directory with a leading slash doesn’t necessarily do what you’d think.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;giallo z-code&quot;&gt;&lt;code data-lang=&quot;python&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source&quot;&gt; os&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source&quot;&gt;os&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation&quot;&gt;.&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source&quot;&gt;path&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation&quot;&gt;.&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-meta z-function-call z-python&quot;&gt;join&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation z-definition z-string z-string&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&#x2F;tmp&#x2F;&amp;quot;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation&quot;&gt;,&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation z-definition z-string z-string&quot;&gt; &amp;quot;other&amp;quot;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation z-definition z-comment z-comment&quot;&gt;# &amp;#39;&#x2F;tmp&#x2F;other&amp;#39;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source&quot;&gt;os&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation&quot;&gt;.&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source&quot;&gt;path&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation&quot;&gt;.&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-meta z-function-call z-python&quot;&gt;join&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation z-definition z-string z-string&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&#x2F;tmp&#x2F;&amp;quot;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation&quot;&gt;,&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation z-definition z-string z-string&quot;&gt; &amp;quot;other&amp;quot;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation z-definition z-comment z-comment&quot;&gt;# &amp;#39;&#x2F;tmp&#x2F;other&amp;#39;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source&quot;&gt;os&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation&quot;&gt;.&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source&quot;&gt;path&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation&quot;&gt;.&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-meta z-function-call z-python&quot;&gt;join&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation z-definition z-string z-string&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&#x2F;tmp&#x2F;&amp;quot;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation&quot;&gt;,&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation z-definition z-string z-string&quot;&gt; &amp;quot;&#x2F;other&amp;quot;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation z-definition z-comment z-comment&quot;&gt;# &amp;#39;&#x2F;other&amp;#39;  (?!)&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;pre&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;giallo z-code&quot;&gt;&lt;code data-lang=&quot;python&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source&quot;&gt; pathlib&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source&quot;&gt;tmp&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-keyword z-operator&quot;&gt; =&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source&quot;&gt; pathlib&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation&quot;&gt;.&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-meta z-function-call z-python&quot;&gt;Path&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation z-definition z-string z-string&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&#x2F;tmp&amp;quot;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source&quot;&gt;other&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-keyword z-operator&quot;&gt; =&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source&quot;&gt; pathlib&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation&quot;&gt;.&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-meta z-function-call z-python&quot;&gt;Path&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation z-definition z-string z-string&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;other&amp;quot;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source&quot;&gt;tmp&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-keyword z-operator&quot;&gt; &#x2F;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source&quot;&gt; other&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation z-definition z-comment z-comment&quot;&gt;# PosixPath(&amp;#39;&#x2F;tmp&#x2F;other&amp;#39;)&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source&quot;&gt;other&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-keyword z-operator&quot;&gt; =&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source&quot;&gt; pathlib&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation&quot;&gt;.&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-meta z-function-call z-python&quot;&gt;Path&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation&quot;&gt;(&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation z-definition z-string z-string&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&#x2F;other&amp;quot;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation&quot;&gt;)&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source&quot;&gt;tmp&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-keyword z-operator&quot;&gt; &#x2F;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source&quot;&gt; other&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;giallo-l&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation z-definition z-comment z-comment&quot;&gt;# PosixPath(&amp;#39;&#x2F;other&amp;#39;)&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;pre&gt;</content>
        <summary type="html">Joining paths with a leading slash overwrite the path they&#x27;re being joined with</summary>
        </entry>
